SIMPLE: uninterested
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uninterested
<hw>Un*in"ter*est*ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Not interested; not having any interest or property in; having
nothing at stake; <as>as, to be <ex>uninterested</ex> in any
business</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not having the mind or the passions engaged; <as>as,
<ex>uninterested</ex> in a discourse or narration</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unintermission</ent>⟦br⟧
